# plugin-loader.js — Plugin Discovery & Lifecycle

## Purpose
Scans `config.plugins` for enabled plugins, dynamically imports them from
`src/node/plugins/{name}/index.js`, and manages their lifecycle.

## Plugin Interface
```
{ init(portalAPI, config), destroy(), onAlert?(alert) }
```

## Exports
- `PluginLoader` class
  - `constructor(config, portalAPI)` — receives full config + portal API object
  - `initAll()` — discover + init all enabled plugins
  - `destroyAll()` — graceful shutdown of all active plugins
  - `dispatchAlert(alert)` — forward system events to plugins with `onAlert()`

## Portal API (passed to plugins)
- `adapterPool` — AdapterPool instance for LLM calls
- `mcpProxy` — MCPProxyManager for tool access
- `broadcast(msg)` — WebSocket broadcast to all monitors

## Alert Schema
```
{ type: 'crash'|'error', server?: string, message: string, ...extra }
```
